        "timestamp": "2020-06-18 12:16:28.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> Do we really need to add such information that may often change during the Release  ?\n> I would avocate for a link towards the gerrit to be always aligned with the code.\n\nI don't think the documentation structure would change that often, so I'd rather leave this info here (links are not very user-friendly, IMO). However, we can reduce the depth of the structure displayed here to just the main categories, if that would be OK? Those should be relatively static, I think.",
